              "type": "prose",
              "html": "Some loops have an awkward shape: you can't check the stopping condition until <em>after</em> you've done part of the work — like reading input. You have to read a value before you can ask \"was that the quit signal?\" This is the <strong>loop-and-a-half</strong> pattern, and it shows up constantly in input handling and games."
            },
