              "type": "heading",
              "text": "The problem"
            },
            {
              "type": "prose",
              "html": "Imagine reading numbers until the user enters <code>-1</code> (a <strong>sentinel</strong> — a special value that means \"stop\"). A plain while loop is clumsy here because the first read has to happen before the first check."
            },
            {
              "type": "heading",
              "text": "Solution: while(true) with break"
            },
            {
              "type": "prose",
              "html": "A clean approach: loop forever, then <code>break</code> out the moment you detect the stop signal. <code>break</code> immediately exits the nearest loop."
            },
            {
              "type": "code",
              "code": "Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);\nint sum = 0;\n\nwhile (true) {\n    System.out.print(\"Enter a number (-1 to stop): \");\n    int n = input.nextInt();\n    if (n == -1) {\n        break;                 // leave the loop right now\n    }\n    sum += n;                  // only runs for real numbers\n}\nSystem.out.println(\"Sum: \" + sum);",
              "out": "Enter a number (-1 to stop): 4\nEnter a number (-1 to stop): 6\nEnter a number (-1 to stop): -1\nSum: 10"
            },
