              "type": "callout",
              "kind": "mistake",
              "title": "Common beginner mistakes",
              "html": "<strong>Processing the sentinel:</strong> make sure your <code>break</code> comes <em>before</em> you use the value, or the stop signal (like -1) gets added into your sum. <strong>Forgetting break entirely:</strong> <code>while (true)</code> with no <code>break</code> is an infinite loop. <strong>break vs continue:</strong> <code>break</code> exits the loop; <code>continue</code> skips to the next pass. Beginners sometimes mix them up."
